.TH "qmi_recv_del_server" 9 "qmi_recv_del_server" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
qmi_recv_del_server \- handler of DEL_SERVER control message
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" qmi_recv_del_server
.BI "(struct qmi_handle *qmi "  ","
.BI "unsigned int node "  ","
.BI "unsigned int port "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "qmi" 12
qmi handle
.IP "node" 12
node of the dying server, a value of -1 matches all nodes
.IP "port" 12
port of the dying server, a value of -1 matches all ports
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Calls the del_server callback for each previously seen server, allowing the
client to react to the disappearing server.
